The course continues the work started in the course Translation from Estonian into English I. Students will continue work on translating non-fiction texts from Estonian into English, with more challenging source texts and greater emphasis on analysis. The texts selected will cover a wide range of topics (politics, business, environment, science, literature and linguistics, etc) and genres (essay, report, academic article, project, legal document, etc). Students will also practice and improve their use of written English, detect problem areas in their language use and learn to overcome their weaknesses.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general aim of Written Translation from Estonian into English is to give the students the possibility to exercise their language abilities in the context of practical translation. The course is aimed for students majoring in English language and Literature.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Written Translation from Estonian into English enhances the students' language skills, brings out individual insufficiencies in the English language usage and helps to deal with lingua-specific difficulties of the transfer from Estonian into English. In addition the students will learn to notice and differentiate and translate different types of texts and language register. The second part of the course Translation from Estonian into English concentrates on the transfer of academic texts from Estonian into English and prepares the students for their final BA thesis.
